Serbia to Give Sitel 750,000 Euros to Open Belgrade Call Center

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-06-22T16:18:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/serbia-to-give-sitel-750-000-euros-to-open-belgrade-call-center.html
Sitel Corp., a U.S. customer-service
company, is to open a call center in Belgrade with state
support,  Serbia ’s government said today.  Serbia will provide a 750,000 euro ($1.08 million)
incentive to Sitel for creating 300 new jobs at the planned 1.25
million euro call center, the country’s Economy Ministry said in
an e-mailed statement ahead of the scheduled signing of the
agreement tomorrow. The planned center is intended for clients
in Western Europe and may expand to 2,000 employees in five
years, the government said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  